            <h3>Our Mission</h3>
            <p>At PIMOSH, we envision a world where every child experiences opportunities to unlock their 
                  full potential and unleash their creativity through the power of arts and technology 
                  education. We believe that every child is capable of greatness and are committed to 
                  empowering, inspiring, and igniting their passions, nurturing their talents, and 
                  encouraging them to dream big. 
              <br />
              <br />
              Together, we will bridge the gap of opportunity, fostering a community where every child 
              is valued, supported, and challenged to achieve their wildest aspirations, where no dream 
              is too big, and no challenge is too great. We will create a brighter future for every 
              child and leave a lasting legacy of innovation, inspiration, and hope.
              </p>
          </div>
          <div id="Diversity" class="tab-pane fade content-text" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="diversity-tab">
            <h3>Diversity Statement</h3>
            <p>Diversity and inclusion are core values of PIMOSH. Every person has unique experiences, 
                  perspectives, and talents that contribute to the richness and strength of our 
                  organization. We are committed to creating an inclusive environment where all 
                  individuals feel respected, valued, and empowered. We actively seek out and welcome 
                  overachieving individuals from diverse backgrounds and experiences and actively work 
                  to remove barriers to participation and success.<br />
              <br />
              We recognize that diversity goes beyond race and ethnicity. It also encompasses 
              differences in gender, age, sexual orientation, socioeconomic status, religion, abilities, 
              and more. We work hard to create a positive, welcoming, and inclusive environment for all 
              members and participants of our organization. We will strive to develop a culture of equity 
              where everyone has an equal opportunity to succeed and feels a sense of belonging.
              <br />
              <br />
              We also acknowledge that inclusion and diversity are ongoing efforts. We will continuously 
              work to identify and address any implicit bias, discrimination, and barriers that prevent 
              individuals from fully participating in our programs and initiatives. We are committed to 
              taking action and being held accountable for creating a genuinely inclusive environment.
              <br />
              <br />
              We believe that embracing diversity and inclusion is not only the right thing to do but 
              also essential to the success of our organization and the communities we serve.
              </p>
          </div>
          <div id="Leadership" class="tab-pane fade content-text" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="leadership-tab">
            <h3>Leadership & Staff Developement</h3>
            <p>At PIMOSH, strong leadership and staff development are crucial to unlocking the full 
                  potential of our programs and the individuals who make them a reality. We are committed 
                  to investing in the growth and development of our program leaders and staff members, 
                  providing them with the tools and resources they need to excel in their roles.
              <br />
              <br />
              We understand that leadership is about having a solid vision and the ability to inspire 
              and empower others to achieve their best. Our leaders are passionate and dedicated individuals 
              committed to creating a culture of excellence where everyone is encouraged to take risks and 
              be innovative.
              <br />
              <br />
              Staff development is necessary for individuals and the organization to succeed. We empower 
              our staff to take ownership of their professional development, providing them with training, 
              mentorship, and networking opportunities. We strive to create a culture of continuous 
              learning where everyone has the opportunity to grow and develop.
              <br />
              <br />
              We know that when our leaders and staff are empowered, motivated and inspired, it positively 
              impacts the communities we serve. Investing in our people enhances our programs' success 
              and creates a brighter future for all.</p>
          </div>
          <div id="Community" class="tab-pane fade content-text" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="community-tab">
            <h3>Community Impact</h3>
            <p>At PIMOSH, our programs and initiatives have the power to make a positive impact on the 
              communities we serve. We are committed to working closely with local organizations, 
              schools, and families to understand our community's unique needs and challenges and 
              to create programs that address them.
              <br />
              <br />
              We strive to create a culture of community engagement, where we actively involve community 
              members in the design, implementation, and evaluation of our programs. Working together 
              with the community can create meaningful and sustainable change that benefits everyone.
              <br />
              <br />
              We understand that our programs go beyond providing access to arts and technology education; 
              they also promote social and emotional well-being, foster creativity, and build self-confidence. 
              Our programs strive to create opportunities for personal growth, achievement, and success 
              for all community members, especially those under-served or marginalized.
              <br />
              <br />
              We are proud of our program's impact on the community and are committed to working with 
              community members to create a brighter future for all.
              <br />
              <br />
              At PIMOSH, our programs and initiatives have the power to make a positive impact on the 
              various communities we serve. We understand that every community is unique, with different 
              needs and challenges. We are committed to working closely with local organizations, schools, 
              and families to understand these needs and design programs that address them. We strive to 
              create a culture of community engagement, where we actively involve community members in the 
              design, implementation, and evaluation of our programs.
              <br />
              <br />
              We are committed to serving diverse communities and understand that diversity goes beyond 
              race and ethnicity. It also encompasses differences in gender, age, sexual orientation, 
              socioeconomic status, religion, abilities, and more. We strive to create opportunities that 
              are inclusive and accessible to all members of the community, especially for those who are 
              underserved or marginalized.
              <br />
